## Limitations

The findings in this report are based on available online resources and may not encompass all perspectives on the topic. The debate on homework is complex and context-dependent, with variations in educational systems, cultural attitudes, and individual student needs influencing the perceived benefits and drawbacks. Additionally, the lack of recent empirical studies specifically addressing the impact of homework on student well-being and academic performance limits the ability to draw definitive conclusions. Further research, particularly longitudinal studies, would be beneficial in providing a more comprehensive understanding of homework's role in education.